    "The results are summarized in Fig. 4e.",
    "Third, biological systems often need to rapidly adapt to changing environments.",
    "A common way to simulate this is 'concept drifting' 31, where a part of the mapping between the output neurons to the seman tic meaning is shuffled regularly, each time a certain number of training iterations has passed (Fig. 4f).",
    "Test error during training with concept drifting is presented in Fig. 4f.",
    "Before epoch 0, both learning rules are initialized with the same pretrained model (trained with backpropa gation); thus, epoch 0 is the first time the model experiences concept drift."
